com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds

Enum AlertSeverity

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AlertSeverity>
      • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds.AlertSeverity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AlertSeverity>

    @ThreadSafety(level=COMPLETELY_THREADSAFE)
public enum AlertSeverity
extends java.lang.Enum<AlertSeverity>
    This class provides information about the types of alert severities that may be included in alert entries.
    NOTE: This class, and other classes within the com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds package structure, are only supported for use against Ping Identity, UnboundID, and Alcatel-Lucent 8661 server products. These classes provide support for proprietary functionality or for external specifications that are not considered stable or mature enough to be guaranteed to work in an interoperable way with other types of LDAP servers.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ERROR
      The alert severity that indicates that the associated alert indicates a non-fatal error has occurred.
      FATAL
      The alert severity that indicates that the associated alert indicates a fatal error has occurred.
      INFO
      The alert severity that indicates that the associated alert is informational.
      WARNING
      The alert severity that indicates that the associated alert indicates a warning has occurred.
